lly considerate neighbors and have had few problems in that area.<br>
<br>
Until now.  Enter new neighbors on the left about 6 months ago.  Since they moved in, i have not had two consecutive full night's sleep.  They consistently wake me up around 2am, their stereo bassing latino dance hall music loud enough that i swear i am inside a club, and the belongings in my bedroom are rattling like the shuttle is taking off next door.  They hang out in the parking lot and on their balcony with their friends, including the loudest, most annoying females on the planet.  They laugh.  They talk.  They scream.  Seriously, the girls fucking SCREAM at 3am.  They break bottles.  They get in their cars and bass those stereos too, and squeal their tires as they spin out, then come back and do it again.  They do this almost EVERY FUCKING NIGHT!  They usually don't stop until about 5am.<br>
<br>
I've complained to the apartment complex about them several times with no results.  We have opened our door and yelled at them to shut up many times, but they either ignore it or can't hear us over themselves.  I've contemplated calling the police, but i know that if i do, the cops will take so long to respond that they'll be gone.  I'm totally at my wits end and sleep deprivation is no fun.  I find myself fantasizing about digging the airplugs out of their tires with a nice sharp knife.  Last night (after they finally shut up) i dreamt that my honey had hired some people to come mess with their cars and i was looking out the window as 2 groups of people in trucks showed up and dissassembled their cars and threw the pieces into the trucks, with the efficiency and speed of a NASCAR pit crew, and then took off.  I tell you, i'm loosing it.  They should consider themselves damn lucky that i don't own a gun because i really, really want to hurt them.  (yes, yes, i wouldn't really, it's just a rant, chill)<br>
<br>
Then, my neighbors on the other side have taken to using our shared stairway landing as their own personal garbage storage area, in direct violation of the lease terms i might add.  And i don't mean they throw a bag out there at night and take it to the dumpster the next day.  Noooo, i mean they put a bag out there and leave it there for a week or so, until i can smell it in the parking lot and there are flys buzzing all around it.  I live in Florida, it is hot and humid and garbage stinks up incredibly quickly.  You know that smell that comes from a well used dumpster in the heat of summer?  Yeh, that smell, i have to walk through that to get into my apartment.  They have taken to leaving trash on the fucking top steps now!  (I picked that shit up and threw it on their welcome mat, what assholes.)  And the worst is that i feel like i can't even complain about these jerks because i have to keep complaining about the fucks on the other side who won't let me sleep, and it will seem like i'm just a bitchy person complaining about everyone, instead of someone trying to get real issues dealt with.  ARRRGGH!<br>
<br>
